#: ../../../hwmon/tmp102.rst:35 ../../../hwmon/tmp102.rst:58
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/tmp102.rst:37
msgid ""
"The Texas Instruments TMP102 implements one temperature sensor.  Limits can "
"be set through the Overtemperature Shutdown register and Hysteresis "
"register.  The sensor is accurate to 0.5 degree over the range of -25 to +85 "
"C, and to 1.0 degree from -40 to +125 C. Resolution of the sensor is 0.0625 "
"degree.  The operating temperature has a minimum of -55 C and a maximum of "
"+150 C."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/tmp102.rst:43
msgid ""
"The TMP102 has a programmable update rate that can select between 8, 4, 1, "
"and 0.25 Hz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../hwmon/tmp102.rst:46
msgid ""
"The TMP110 and TMP113 are software compatible with TMP102, but have "
"different accuracy (maximum error) specifications. The TMP110 has an "
"accuracy (maximum error) of 1.0 degree, TMP113 has an accuracy (maximum "
"error) of 0.3 degree, while TMP102 has an accuracy (maximum error) of 2.0 "
"degree."
msgstr ""

